==English==
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'pætrɒnajz/

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''pater'' meaning father, with the -ize suffix used to create the verb form.
===Verb===
'''patronize''', '''patronise''' (''Australia'')
# make a [[patron]]
# Treat as inferior unduly, talk down to, treat condescendingly.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[tukea]] (1), [[kannattaa]] (1), [[suojella]] (1), [[holhota]] (2)

